  "text": "This bound is tight if f (Pt )/f (t ) = 1 for P ≥ 1. For example, B( f ) = 1 − 1/e for the function f (t ) = min{t, 1}. Note that the approximation ratio of 1 − 1/e ≈ 0.632 for maximization problems of this form was previously known (see Calinescu et al. [CITATION_1] ). However, for some concave functions f , we get a better approximation. For example, for f (t ) = √ t, we get an approximation ratio of B( √ t ) ≈ 0.773. ",
